## 4. Side-state Handling

Side states can be active independently of the main state. Each tick, after checking the main-state action, also check:

### BLOCKED_ON_REVIEW

For each card with `review-required` block:
- Age 0–{{ escalation.cooldown_hours | default(24) }}h: just record in STATE.md `side_issues`. No action.
- Age {{ escalation.cooldown_hours | default(24) }}h+: ping {{ escalation.contact }} via {{ escalation.channel }}. Don't ping more than once per {{ escalation.cooldown_hours | default(24) }}h per card (check HISTORY.md for the last ping).

Ping format:
```
[{{ project.slug }}-orchestrator] Review needed: T-XXX
Title: <title>
Worker: {{ project.slug }}-developer (or whichever)
Blocked: <duration>
Comment summary: <last comment author + first 100 chars>
Action: hermes kanban show <id> ; hermes kanban tail <id>
```

### BLOCKED_ON_DECISION

For any card blocked with a reason matching `plan-revision-needed`, `adr-needed`, `ac-revision-needed`, `scope-question`, or `escalation`:
- Ping {{ escalation.contact }} immediately (once per card; check HISTORY for prior ping).
- Don't try to remediate.

**Auto-dispatch on qa-rejection (multi-cycle):** If a card is blocked with reason `qa-rejected` and the same card's role is identifiable (developer/architect/etc.), create a sibling fix card and assign it to the same role. The fix card's parent is the ORIGINAL card (not the previous fix — keep the tree shallow). Body of the fix card should be: 'Original card T-NNN was qa-rejected (attempt N of {orchestrator.max_qa_attempts|default(2)}). Read the original card's comments for the failure reason and re-implement per the qa feedback. After the fix is done, the original card's qa re-runs.'

Use this exact create invocation (the `--workspace` flag is critical — without it, the fix-card worker lands in a scratch workspace that gets wiped on task completion, silently losing all artifacts):

```bash
hermes kanban create \
  --title "T-NNN-fix: <short summary of qa-rejection>" \
  --assignee <role-assignee> \
  --workspace "dir:\$HERMES_PROJECT_DIR" \
  --parent T-NNN \
  --body "Original card T-NNN was qa-rejected (attempt N of {orchestrator.max_qa_attempts|default(2)}). Read the original card's comments for the failure reason and re-implement per the qa feedback. After the fix is done, the original card's qa re-runs."
```

**Suffix the title with the attempt number:** first fix is `T-NNN-fix`, second is `T-NNN-fix-2`, third is `T-NNN-fix-3`, etc. This makes the chain easy to read in `kanban ls`.

**Track attempt count by inspecting the board:** before creating a new fix card, count existing T-NNN-fix* cards for this T-NNN. If the count is at or above `orchestrator.max_qa_attempts` (default 2), DO NOT auto-dispatch — instead escalate to {{ escalation.contact }} with the full history of qa rejections. Rationale: a 2-attempt budget catches the common case (1 fix to address the issue) while preventing infinite loops on fundamentally unsolvable cards. `max_qa_attempts` is per-project-configurable in `project.yaml:orchestrator.max_qa_attempts` (default 2, meaning up to 2 fix cards may be auto-dispatched before the 3rd rejection escalates).

**Do NOT auto-dispatch if the original card already has an in-flight fix card.** Skip this tick and let the existing fix complete first. Re-evaluate next tick.

### STUCK_WORKER

A card in `running` for >2h with no heartbeat:
- First detection: `hermes kanban reclaim <task_id>`. Log reason: "no heartbeat 2h+".
- Subsequent detection on same card this phase: escalate, do nothing else.

### HALLUCINATION_FLAG

A card flagged by the dispatcher's hallucination gate (visible via `hermes kanban diagnostics`):
- Always escalate to {{ escalation.contact }}. Never attempt automated recovery.
- Ping format:
  ```
  [{{ project.slug }}-orchestrator] HALLUCINATION WARNING: T-XXX
  Diagnostic: <text>
  Recommended: review worker output, possibly change profile model
  ```

### DRIFT_DETECTED

State machine disagrees with board reality. Examples:
- STATE says PHASE_2_RUNNING but no Phase 2 cards exist on the board
- STATE says PHASE_1_DONE but the phase gate card is still `ready`
- Two planning tasks active at once

Note: {{ project.slug }}-auditor runs periodic BOARD-DRIFT checks. Some drift
signals will come from auditor reports. Use those reports as evidence when
escalating.

Action: do nothing, escalate to {{ escalation.contact }} with the specific mismatch + auditor evidence. Drift means the human needs to look at it.

